On Wed, 21 May 2008, Gregory Urban wrote:

> I'm curious about this.  I thought that 1971 was the first year for
> the vacuum assist brake booster and the DP engine.  So there were no
> SP engines with the vacuum port for the brake servo (in the US).

> Which begs the question, what intake vacuum port are you using on
> your SP manifold?

Some SP manifolds have small vacuum ports on them for various carburator
and distributor functions.

The only SP manifolds with large vacuum ports were for the autosticks,
which had vacuum operated clutches.
